112static void
113gf100_ram_train(struct gf100_ramfuc *fuc, u32 magic)
114{
115 struct gf100_ram *ram = container_of(fuc, typeof(*ram), fuc);
116 struct nvkm_fb *fb = ram->base.fb;
117 struct nvkm_device *device = fb->subdev.device;
118 u32 part = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x022438), i;
119 u32 mask = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x022554);
120 u32 addr = 0x110974;
121
122 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f910, magic);
123 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f914, magic);
124
125 for (i = 0; (magic & 0x80000000) && i < part; addr += 0x1000, i++) {
126 if (mask & (1 << i))
127 continue;
128 ram_wait(fuc, addr, 0x0000000f, 0x00000000, 500000);
129 }
130}

132static int
133gf100_ram_calc(struct nvkm_ram *base, u32 freq)
134{
135 struct gf100_ram *ram = gf100_ram(base);
136 struct gf100_ramfuc *fuc = &ram->fuc;
137 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &ram->base.fb->subdev;
138 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
139 struct nvkm_clk *clk = device->clk;
140 struct nvkm_bios *bios = device->bios;
141 struct nvbios_ramcfg cfg;
142 u8 ver, cnt, len, strap;
143 struct {
144 u32 data;
145 u8 size;
146 } rammap, ramcfg, timing;
147 int ref, div, out;
148 int from, mode;
149 int N1, M1, P;
150 int ret;
151
152 /* lookup memory config data relevant to the target frequency */
153 rammap.data = nvbios_rammapEm(bios, freq / 1000, &ver, &rammap.size,
154 &cnt, &ramcfg.size, &cfg);
155 if (!rammap.data || ver != 0x10 || rammap.size < 0x0e) {
156 nvkm_error(subdev, "invalid/missing rammap entry\n");
157 return -EINVAL;
158 }
159
160 /* locate specific data set for the attached memory */
161 strap = nvbios_ramcfg_index(subdev);
162 if (strap >= cnt) {
163 nvkm_error(subdev, "invalid ramcfg strap\n");
164 return -EINVAL;
165 }
166
167 ramcfg.data = rammap.data + rammap.size + (strap * ramcfg.size);
168 if (!ramcfg.data || ver != 0x10 || ramcfg.size < 0x0e) {
169 nvkm_error(subdev, "invalid/missing ramcfg entry\n");
170 return -EINVAL;
171 }
172
173 /* lookup memory timings, if bios says they're present */
174 strap = nvbios_rd08(bios, ramcfg.data + 0x01);
175 if (strap != 0xff) {
176 timing.data = nvbios_timingEe(bios, strap, &ver, &timing.size,
177 &cnt, &len);
178 if (!timing.data || ver != 0x10 || timing.size < 0x19) {
179 nvkm_error(subdev, "invalid/missing timing entry\n");
180 return -EINVAL;
181 }
182 } else {
183 timing.data = 0;
184 }
185
186 ret = ram_init(fuc, ram->base.fb);
187 if (ret)
188 return ret;
189
190 /* determine current mclk configuration */
191 from = !!(ram_rd32(fuc, 0x1373f0) & 0x00000002); /*XXX: ok? */
192
193 /* determine target mclk configuration */
194 if (!(ram_rd32(fuc, 0x137300) & 0x00000100))
195 ref = nvkm_clk_read(clk, nv_clk_src_sppll0);
196 else
197 ref = nvkm_clk_read(clk, nv_clk_src_sppll1);
198 div = max(min((ref * 2) / freq, (u32)65), (u32)2) - 2;
199 out = (ref * 2) / (div + 2);
200 mode = freq != out;
201
202 ram_mask(fuc, 0x137360, 0x00000002, 0x00000000);
203
204 if ((ram_rd32(fuc, 0x132000) & 0x00000002) || 0 /*XXX*/) {
205 ram_nuke(fuc, 0x132000);
206 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132000, 0x00000002, 0x00000002);
207 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132000, 0x00000002, 0x00000000);
208 }
209
210 if (mode == 1) {
211 ram_nuke(fuc, 0x10fe20);
212 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10fe20, 0x00000002, 0x00000002);
213 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10fe20, 0x00000002, 0x00000000);
214 }
215
216// 0x00020034 // 0x0000000a
217 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x132100, 0x00000001);
218
219 if (mode == 1 && from == 0) {
220 /* calculate refpll */
221 ret = gt215_pll_calc(subdev, &ram->refpll, ram->mempll.refclk,
222 &N1, NULL, &M1, &P);
223 if (ret <= 0) {
224 nvkm_error(subdev, "unable to calc refpll\n");
225 return ret ? ret : -ERANGE;
226 }
227
228 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10fe20, 0x20010000);
229 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x137320, 0x00000003);
230 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x137330, 0x81200006);
231 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10fe24, (P << 16) | (N1 << 8) | M1);
232 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10fe20, 0x20010001);
233 ram_wait(fuc, 0x137390, 0x00020000, 0x00020000, 64000);
234
235 /* calculate mempll */
236 ret = gt215_pll_calc(subdev, &ram->mempll, freq,
237 &N1, NULL, &M1, &P);
238 if (ret <= 0) {
239 nvkm_error(subdev, "unable to calc refpll\n");
240 return ret ? ret : -ERANGE;
241 }
242
243 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10fe20, 0x20010005);
244 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x132004, (P << 16) | (N1 << 8) | M1);
245 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x132000, 0x18010101);
246 ram_wait(fuc, 0x137390, 0x00000002, 0x00000002, 64000);
247 } else
248 if (mode == 0) {
249 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x137300, 0x00000003);
250 }
251
252 if (from == 0) {
253 ram_nuke(fuc, 0x10fb04);
254 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10fb04, 0x0000ffff, 0x00000000);
255 ram_nuke(fuc, 0x10fb08);
256 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10fb08, 0x0000ffff, 0x00000000);
257 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f988, 0x2004ff00);
258 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f98c, 0x003fc040);
259 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f990, 0x20012001);
260 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f998, 0x00011a00);
261 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x13d8f4, 0x00000000);
262 } else {
263 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f988, 0x20010000);
264 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f98c, 0x00000000);
265 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f990, 0x20012001);
266 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f998, 0x00010a00);
267 }
268
269 if (from == 0) {
270// 0x00020039 // 0x000000ba
271 }
272
273// 0x0002003a // 0x00000002
274 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x100b0c, 0x00080012);
275// 0x00030014 // 0x00000000 // 0x02b5f070
276// 0x00030014 // 0x00010000 // 0x02b5f070
277 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x611200, 0x00003300);
278// 0x00020034 // 0x0000000a
279// 0x00030020 // 0x00000001 // 0x00000000
280
281 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x00000800, 0x00000000);
282 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f210, 0x00000000);
283 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
284 if (mode == 0)
285 gf100_ram_train(fuc, 0x000c1001);
286 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f310, 0x00000001);
287 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
288 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f090, 0x00000061);
289 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f090, 0xc000007f);
290 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
291
292 if (from == 0) {
293 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f824, 0x00007fd4);
294 } else {
295 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x1373ec, 0x00020404);
296 }
297
298 if (mode == 0) {
299 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f808, 0x00080000, 0x00000000);
300 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x00008000, 0x00008000);
301 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x41500010);
302 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x01000000, 0x00000000);
303 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132100, 0x00000100, 0x00000100);
304 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f050, 0xff000090);
305 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x1373ec, 0x00020f0f);
306 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x1373f0, 0x00000003);
307 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x137310, 0x81201616);
308 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x132100, 0x00000001);
309// 0x00020039 // 0x000000ba
310 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x00300017);
311 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x1373f0, 0x00000001);
312 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f824, 0x00007e77);
313 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x132000, 0x18030001);
314 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f090, 0x4000007e);
315 ram_nsec(fuc, 2000);
316 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f314, 0x00000001);
317 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f210, 0x80000000);
318 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f338, 0x00300220);
319 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f300, 0x0000011d);
320 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
321 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f290, 0x02060505);
322 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f294, 0x34208288);
323 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f298, 0x44050411);
324 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f29c, 0x0000114c);
325 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f2a0, 0x42e10069);
326 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f614, 0x40044f77);
327 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f610, 0x40044f77);
328 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f344, 0x00600009);
329 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
330 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f348, 0x00700008);
331 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x61c140, 0x19240000);
332 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x00300017);
333 gf100_ram_train(fuc, 0x80021001);
334 gf100_ram_train(fuc, 0x80081001);
335 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f340, 0x00500004);
336 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
337 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x01300017);
338 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x00300017);
339// 0x00030020 // 0x00000000 // 0x00000000
340// 0x00020034 // 0x0000000b
341 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x100b0c, 0x00080028);
342 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x611200, 0x00003330);
343 } else {
344 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f800, 0x00001800);
345 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x13d8f4, 0x00000000);
346 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x1373ec, 0x00020404);
347 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x1373f0, 0x00000003);
348 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x40700010);
349 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x40500010);
350 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x13d8f4, 0x00000000);
351 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x1373f8, 0x00000000);
352 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x132100, 0x00000101);
353 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x137310, 0x89201616);
354 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f050, 0xff000090);
355 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x1373ec, 0x00030404);
356 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x1373f0, 0x00000002);
357 // 0x00020039 // 0x00000011
358 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x132100, 0x00000001);
359 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x1373f8, 0x00002000);
360 ram_nsec(fuc, 2000);
361 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f808, 0x7aaa0050);
362 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x00500010);
363 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x00ce1000);
364 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f090, 0x4000007e);
365 ram_nsec(fuc, 2000);
366 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f314, 0x00000001);
367 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f210, 0x80000000);
368 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f338, 0x00300200);
369 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f300, 0x0000084d);
370 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
371 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f290, 0x0b343825);
372 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f294, 0x3483028e);
373 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f298, 0x440c0600);
374 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f29c, 0x0000214c);
375 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f2a0, 0x42e20069);
376 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x00ce0000);
377 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f614, 0x60044e77);
378 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f610, 0x60044e77);
379 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f340, 0x00500000);
380 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
381 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f344, 0x00600228);
382 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
383 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f348, 0x00700000);
384 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x13d8f4, 0x00000000);
385 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x61c140, 0x09a40000);
386
387 gf100_ram_train(fuc, 0x800e1008);
388
389 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
390 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f800, 0x00001804);
391 // 0x00030020 // 0x00000000 // 0x00000000
392 // 0x00020034 // 0x0000000b
393 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x13d8f4, 0x00000000);
394 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x100b0c, 0x00080028);
395 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x611200, 0x00003330);
396 ram_nsec(fuc, 100000);
397 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f9b0, 0x05313f41);
398 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f9b4, 0x00002f50);
399
400 gf100_ram_train(fuc, 0x010c1001);
401 }
402
403 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x00000800, 0x00000800);
404// 0x00020016 // 0x00000000
405
406 if (mode == 0)
407 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132000, 0x00000001, 0x00000000);
408
409 return 0;
410}

412static int
413gf100_ram_prog(struct nvkm_ram *base)
414{
415 struct gf100_ram *ram = gf100_ram(base);
416 struct nvkm_device *device = ram->base.fb->subdev.device;
417 ram_exec(&ram->fuc, nvkm_boolopt(device->cfgopt, "NvMemExec", true));
418 return 0;
419}
420
421static void
422gf100_ram_tidy(struct nvkm_ram *base)
423{
424 struct gf100_ram *ram = gf100_ram(base);
425 ram_exec(&ram->fuc, false);
426}
427
428extern const u8 gf100_pte_storage_type_map[256];
429
430void
431gf100_ram_put(struct nvkm_ram *ram, struct nvkm_mem **pmem)
432{
433 struct nvkm_ltc *ltc = ram->fb->subdev.device->ltc;
434 struct nvkm_mem *mem = *pmem;
435
436 *pmem = NULL;
437 if (unlikely(mem == NULL))
438 return;
439
440 mutex_lock(&ram->fb->subdev.mutex);
441 if (mem->tag)
442 nvkm_ltc_tags_free(ltc, &mem->tag);
443 __nv50_ram_put(ram, mem);
444 mutex_unlock(&ram->fb->subdev.mutex);
445
446 kfree(mem);
447}
448
449int
450gf100_ram_get(struct nvkm_ram *ram, u64 size, u32 align, u32 ncmin,
451 u32 memtype, struct nvkm_mem **pmem)
452{
453 struct nvkm_ltc *ltc = ram->fb->subdev.device->ltc;
454 struct nvkm_mm *mm = &ram->vram;
455 struct nvkm_mm_node *r;
456 struct nvkm_mem *mem;
457 int type = (memtype & 0x0ff);
458 int back = (memtype & 0x800);
459 const bool comp = gf100_pte_storage_type_map[type] != type;
460 int ret;
461
462 size >>= NVKM_RAM_MM_SHIFT;
463 align >>= NVKM_RAM_MM_SHIFT;
464 ncmin >>= NVKM_RAM_MM_SHIFT;
465 if (!ncmin)
466 ncmin = size;
467
468 mem = kzalloc(sizeof(*mem), GFP_KERNEL);
469 if (!mem)
470 return -ENOMEM;
471
472 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&mem->regions);
473 mem->size = size;
474
475 mutex_lock(&ram->fb->subdev.mutex);
476 if (comp) {
477 /* compression only works with lpages */
478 if (align == (1 << (17 - NVKM_RAM_MM_SHIFT))) {
479 int n = size >> 5;
480 nvkm_ltc_tags_alloc(ltc, n, &mem->tag);
481 }
482
483 if (unlikely(!mem->tag))
484 type = gf100_pte_storage_type_map[type];
485 }
486 mem->memtype = type;
487
488 do {
489 if (back)
490 ret = nvkm_mm_tail(mm, 0, 1, size, ncmin, align, &r);
491 else
492 ret = nvkm_mm_head(mm, 0, 1, size, ncmin, align, &r);
493 if (ret) {
494 mutex_unlock(&ram->fb->subdev.mutex);
495 ram->func->put(ram, &mem);
496 return ret;
497 }
498
499 list_add_tail(&r->rl_entry, &mem->regions);
500 size -= r->length;
501 } while (size);
502 mutex_unlock(&ram->fb->subdev.mutex);
503
504 r = list_first_entry(&mem->regions, struct nvkm_mm_node, rl_entry);
505 mem->offset = (u64)r->offset << NVKM_RAM_MM_SHIFT;
506 *pmem = mem;
507 return 0;
508}
509
510static int
511gf100_ram_init(struct nvkm_ram *base)
512{
513 static const u8 train0[] = {
514 0x00, 0xff, 0x55, 0xaa, 0x33, 0xcc,
515 0x00, 0xff, 0xff, 0x00, 0xff, 0x00,
516 };
517 static const u32 train1[] = {
518 0x00000000, 0xffffffff,
519 0x55555555, 0xaaaaaaaa,
520 0x33333333, 0xcccccccc,
521 0xf0f0f0f0, 0x0f0f0f0f,
522 0x00ff00ff, 0xff00ff00,
523 0x0000ffff, 0xffff0000,
524 };
525 struct gf100_ram *ram = gf100_ram(base);
526 struct nvkm_device *device = ram->base.fb->subdev.device;
527 int i;
528
529 switch (ram->base.type) {
530 case NVKM_RAM_TYPE_GDDR5:
531 break;
532 default:
533 return 0;
534 }
535
536 /* prepare for ddr link training, and load training patterns */
537 for (i = 0; i < 0x30; i++) {
538 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10f968, 0x00000000 | (i << 8));
539 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10f96c, 0x00000000 | (i << 8));
540 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10f920, 0x00000100 | train0[i % 12]);
541 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10f924, 0x00000100 | train0[i % 12]);
542 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10f918, train1[i % 12]);
543 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10f91c, train1[i % 12]);
544 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10f920, 0x00000000 | train0[i % 12]);
545 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10f924, 0x00000000 | train0[i % 12]);
546 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10f918, train1[i % 12]);
547 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10f91c, train1[i % 12]);
548 }
549
550 return 0;
551}
552
553static const struct nvkm_ram_func
554gf100_ram_func = {
555 .init = gf100_ram_init,
556 .get = gf100_ram_get,
557 .put = gf100_ram_put,
558 .calc = gf100_ram_calc,
559 .prog = gf100_ram_prog,
560 .tidy = gf100_ram_tidy,
561};
562
563int
564gf100_ram_ctor(const struct nvkm_ram_func *func, struct nvkm_fb *fb,
565 u32 maskaddr, struct nvkm_ram *ram)
566{
567 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fb->subdev;
568 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
569 struct nvkm_bios *bios = device->bios;
570 const u32 rsvd_head = ( 256 * 1024); /* vga memory */
571 const u32 rsvd_tail = (1024 * 1024); /* vbios etc */
572 u32 parts = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x022438);
573 u32 pmask = nvkm_rd32(device, maskaddr);
574 u64 bsize = (u64)nvkm_rd32(device, 0x10f20c) << 20;
575 u64 psize, size = 0;
576 enum nvkm_ram_type type = nvkm_fb_bios_memtype(bios);
577 bool uniform = true;
578 int ret, i;
579
580 nvkm_debug(subdev, "100800: %08x\n", nvkm_rd32(device, 0x100800));
581 nvkm_debug(subdev, "parts %08x mask %08x\n", parts, pmask);
582
583 /* read amount of vram attached to each memory controller */
584 for (i = 0; i < parts; i++) {
585 if (pmask & (1 << i))
586 continue;
587
588 psize = (u64)nvkm_rd32(device, 0x11020c + (i * 0x1000)) << 20;
589 if (psize != bsize) {
590 if (psize < bsize)
591 bsize = psize;
592 uniform = false;
593 }
594
595 nvkm_debug(subdev, "%d: %d MiB\n", i, (u32)(psize >> 20));
596 size += psize;
597 }
598
599 ret = nvkm_ram_ctor(func, fb, type, size, 0, ram);
600 if (ret)
601 return ret;
602
603 nvkm_mm_fini(&ram->vram);
604
605 /* if all controllers have the same amount attached, there's no holes */
606 if (uniform) {
607 ret = nvkm_mm_init(&ram->vram, rsvd_head >> NVKM_RAM_MM_SHIFT,
608 (size - rsvd_head - rsvd_tail) >>
609 NVKM_RAM_MM_SHIFT, 1);
610 if (ret)
611 return ret;
612 } else {
613 /* otherwise, address lowest common amount from 0GiB */
614 ret = nvkm_mm_init(&ram->vram, rsvd_head >> NVKM_RAM_MM_SHIFT,
615 ((bsize * parts) - rsvd_head) >>
616 NVKM_RAM_MM_SHIFT, 1);
617 if (ret)
618 return ret;
619
620 /* and the rest starting from (8GiB + common_size) */
621 ret = nvkm_mm_init(&ram->vram, (0x0200000000ULL + bsize) >>
622 NVKM_RAM_MM_SHIFT,
623 (size - (bsize * parts) - rsvd_tail) >>
624 NVKM_RAM_MM_SHIFT, 1);
625 if (ret)
626 return ret;
627 }
628
629 ram->ranks = (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x10f200) & 0x00000004) ? 2 : 1;
630 return 0;
631}
632
633int
634gf100_ram_new(struct nvkm_fb *fb, struct nvkm_ram **pram)
635{
636 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fb->subdev;
637 struct nvkm_bios *bios = subdev->device->bios;
638 struct gf100_ram *ram;
639 int ret;
640
641 if (!(ram = kzalloc(sizeof(*ram), GFP_KERNEL)))
642 return -ENOMEM;
643 *pram = &ram->base;
644
645 ret = gf100_ram_ctor(&gf100_ram_func, fb, 0x022554, &ram->base);
646 if (ret)
647 return ret;
648
649 ret = nvbios_pll_parse(bios, 0x0c, &ram->refpll);
650 if (ret) {
651 nvkm_error(subdev, "mclk refpll data not found\n");
652 return ret;
653 }

655 ret = nvbios_pll_parse(bios, 0x04, &ram->mempll);
